5:
It has been a pleasure, but it's time
for us to go.
8:
It's probably been more of a
pleasure for us than it's been for
you. Seriously, thanks for helping us
out.
13:
Hopefully the next time we drop by,
things'll have calmed down... We'll
bring Nephtim with us too.
17:
I suspect meeting again will be
difficult. We will be abandoning this
hideout in the near future.
21:
Since we stirred up too much of a
fuss, we're gonna lie low for a while.
29:
Yeah, we'll see each other again
somehow. Just gotta weather this
storm and make it out the other side
first.
39:
Sotieth, remember what I said! Live
your life without regrets, okay?
48:
Just can't help wondering if Rashid
and the others will be okay...
52: I get where you're coming fromâ€”
68:
Are... Are those the kingdom's
soldiers?!
71:
This doesn't bode well... They're
headed straight for the Golden
Dawn's base!
80: Wait. I think it's better if we...
84:
Hahaha... An excellent proposal.
Very well, I agree to this plan!
88:
Leave the sanctuary of our
comrades to me. I shall unleash the
depths of my darkest abilities on our
unsuspecting foes!
92: You guys be careful too, okay?
102: Go! I shall attack with you!
106:
Sheesh... I can't believe they found
us so fast!
109:
Rashid, bad news! More of them are
pouring in from the west entrance!
113:
Blow up the western passageways
and seal them out! Once you've
done that, find another entrance
and run!
116:
How did they even find us in the first
place?
119:
Searching hiding spots one by one
would definitely take a while.
122:
It's much easier to use all hands at
your disposal to clear out every
hiding hole at once.
124:
The kingdom has enough man
power to do so.
137:
This power... It's as I suspected.
You're no mere human.
140:
I thought it was just a myth that the
ancients built human-like super
weapons... But I'm not surprised to
see this is how Rashid finally
obtained power.
144:
Why, Haridal... Why are you doing
this?
148:
To fulfill the oath we made together
that day.
151:
I'll carve a future for the
borderlands... I'm just doing so from
inside the kingdom.
159:
Are you blind? Look at all this
bloodshed! How can you claim this
is for anyone's future!
167:
After what the Golden Dawn did, the
kingdom will treat the borderlands
even worse from now on.
170:
The only way to placate them is to
make an example of you and yours.
174:
You did this... just to please your
masters?
178:
This is your own doing. You raised
your weapons first... Something I
thought you'd never do.
181:
You've changed for the worse,
Rashid. Not me. I've stayed true to
my ideals.
186:
What was I supposed to have
done?! Just accept that the
kingdom was enslaving our people?
Turn a blind eye and let my brothers
and sisters suffer?
195: Maybe you can do that... But not me.
199:
I know. That's the kind of guy you
are. You'd never leave a single
person behind to suffer.
201:
That's exactly why you're unfit to
wield any power...
216:
Nimbus? Everyone! What are you
doing here?
220:
My guilty conscience would've eaten
me alive if I'd abandoned you guys.
225:
So you're the Hellcat of the Dunes.
Finally, a worthy opponent.
228:
I'll do my duty as a kingdom soldier...
Take out the Golden Dawn and your
weapon of the ancients...
231:
Then I'll be one step closer to
fulfilling the oath I made with you!
